Check present working directory - pwd
See content/List content - ls
See content/List content with more details - ls -l
See content/List content of hidden files - ls -a
Create Directory - mkdir <DirectoryName> mkdir folder1 folder2 / mkdir folder3/folder4 | mkdir -p /UncreatedFolder1/UncreatedFolder2 (-p for parent directory)
Go back to home directory directly - cd
Go back to 1 directory backward - cd .. 
Get inside a directory - cd <DirectoryName>
push and pop directory - pushd/popd
Move Directory - mv /home/aatif/Europe/Morocco /home/aatif/Africa/
Rename Directory - mv /Asis/India/MOOMbai /Asia/India/Mumbai
Copy file - cp Asia/India/Mumbai/city.txt Africa/Egypt/Cairo
Delete/Remove file - rm Europe/UK/london/Tottenham.txt
Read file - cat Asia/India/Mumbai/city.txt
Write in file - cat > Africa/Egypt/Cairo/City.txt  add lines afterwards then ctrl + D
Create empty file - touch /Asia/China/Country.txt
Reading long long files - more bigbigfile.txt | less bigbigfile.txt
To list all the files in the order they were modified - ls -lt 
To list all the files form oldest to newest - ls -ltr

Command line help e.g. - whatis date | man date | date --help | apropos modpr


